						               													<description>Egri Csillagok is a cooperative board game for 4-6 people, which evokes the spirit of the heroes of Eger and G&amp;eacute;za G&amp;aacute;rdonyi. The players play the roles of the defenders of the castle, i.e. the protagonists of the famous novel, such as Dob&amp;oacute;, Mekcsey, Bornemissza, and their goal is to keep the Turkish attackers outside the walls. To do this, they not only have to repel the continuous Turkish attacks against the walls, but they also have to neutralize the minework of the traitor(s) inside. In each round, four events occur at the four wall sections of the castle, for the solution of which cards must be submitted secretly, and the success of the defense depends on their results. If you succeed in handing in the cards corresponding to the prescribed task together, the defenders will receive a reward, otherwise the Turkish armies will approach the inner castle, the will to fight will deteriorate, or the players will suffer dangerous injuries.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
